    <h1>Towers of Hanoi</h1>
    <h4>
      Rules: <br />Three pegs are available, labeled 1, 2, and 3. <br />The
      disks vary in size(1-5) and are initially stacked in ascending order on
      peg 1. <br />
      Only onedisk can be moved at a time. <br />
      Larger disks cannot be placed on top of smaller disks. <br />
      You must move the topmost disk from any peg to any othern peg. <br />
      The final arrangement should be all 5 disks stacked in ascending order on
      peg 3. <br />
      Minimum number of moves required to solve it is 31.<br />
      Open Console to & click display board to play! <br />
    </h4>
    <h5>
      Peg 1 --- <br />
      Peg 2 --- <br />
      Peg 3 --- <br />
    </h5>
    <button onclick="moveDisc(1,2)">Move Disc 1 to 2</button>
    <button onclick="moveDisc(1,3)">Move Disc 1 to 3</button> <br />
    <button onclick="moveDisc(2,1)">Move Disc 2 to 1</button>
    <button onclick="moveDisc(2,3)">Move Disc 2 to 3</button> <br />
    <button onclick="moveDisc(3,2)">Move Disc 3 to 2</button>
    <button onclick="moveDisc(3,1)">Move Disc 3 to 1</button> <br />
    <button onclick="displayBoard()">Display Current Board</button>
    <button onclick="resetGame()">Reset Game</button>
    <button onclick="checkWinner()">Check Winner</button>
    <article>
      <h2></h2>
      <label>User Input:</label>
      <input type="text" placeholder="Give us feedback" maxlength="12" /><input
